node.text:
I believe in you.🔥 Whatever you're feeling right now. Whatever you're set out to accomplish or do today, just know, you can do it.
.
It doesn't matter what other people say about you.
.
It doesn't matter what kind of family you came from.
.
It doesn't matter how much money you had growing up, I believe in you.
.
And having the belief of someone else is one of the most powerful things in the world.
.
So today, if you're feeling weak. If things aren't going your way. Or if you're thinking about giving up...
.
Borrow my belief.
.
Push through.
.
And if you're feeling like you need more direction in your life or you just don't know where to get started and wants to know the best skill to get you your freedom...
.
Click the in my bio!
.
I believe in you with every fibre of my being, and I want to see you succeed.
.
So for me to help you do that, go to the link in my bio and check out the FREE masterclass I'm putting on. In it, you’ll discover the #1 skill.
.
As you go about your day, keep this post in mind.
.
When you feel like giving up, or not going the extra mile, keep this post in mind.
.
And if you are thinking about not giving it your best, keep this post in mind, too.
.
Comment below, "I can do it!" to charge yourself up for the rest of the day

node.text:
Hmmmm… I’m not sure if I fully agree with this video. Money is absolutely a great tool that can be used for the greater good. There are so many amazing people that donate their money to organizations and people that save lives and the planet.
However, Gandhi, MLK, Mother Theresa, School Teachers, first responders, nurses and so many others have changed the world with little to no money as well.
Can you imagine how much worse this world would be if the everyday heroes used the excuse that they cant help because they don’t have any money??
Anyway, that’s my thoughts on this video. 
Maybe I’m wrong, maybe I’m right. What do you think?

node.text:
It’s a lot easier to love others when you start with yourself.

Listen .. all of us have plenty of shortcomings ... but the key 🔑 is understanding that everyone else has them too and to work from a place of kindness on yourself and others... once you understand “self love” which is very different than “delusional thinking” you have capacity to love others, which in turn makes the world 🌍 around you a much kinder and better place ☀️❤️

node.text:
Making a sale is great, but a sale isn’t a sale until it sticks.

If your customer or client is just going to refund, you’ve wasted your time.

It will pay you to turn each sale into a valued customer.

Someone you take care of and help solve their problems.

After all, that’s what they are paying you for.

You must go above and beyond for every person that comes through your business.

This is one of the keys to running a highly profitable business.

And if you want to build a highly profitable business in 2021, then you’ll want to join our next free training link in my bio!

Comment below “I’m a winner” if you’re a champion!

See you there
